Author-Name: Diego Comin  
Author-Name: Bart Hobijn  
Title: An Exploration of Technology Diffusion 
Abstract:
 We develop a model that, at the aggregate level, is similar to the
 one-sector neoclassical growth model; at the disaggregate level, it has
 implications for the path of observable measures of technology adoption.
 We estimate it using data on the diffusion of 15 technologies in 166
 countries over the last two centuries. Our results reveal that, on
 average, countries have adopted technologies 45  years after their
 invention. There is substantial variation across technologies and
 countries. Newer technologies have been adopted faster than old ones. The
 cross-country variation in the adoption of technologies accounts for at
 least 25  percent of per capita income differences. (JEL O33, O41, O47)
