Author-Name: Ron Siegel  
Title: Asymmetric Contests with Conditional Investments 
Abstract:
 This paper studies equilibrium behavior in a class of games that models
 asymmetric competitions with unconditional and conditional investments.
 Such competitions include lobbying settings, labor-market tournaments, and
 R& races, among others. I provide an algorithm that constructs the unique
 equilibrium in these games and apply it to study competitions in which a
 fraction of each competitor's investment is sunk and the rest is paid only
 by the winners. Complete-information all-pay auctions are a special case.
 (JEL D44, D72, D82)
