Author-Name: Fabian Herweg  
Author-Name: Daniel Muller  
Author-Name: Philipp Weinschenk  
Title: Binary Payment Schemes: Moral Hazard and Loss Aversion 
Abstract:
 We modify the principal-agent model with moral hazard by assuming that the
  agent is expectation-based loss averse according to Koszegi and
 Rabin (2006, 2007). The optimal contract is a binary payment scheme even
 for a rich performance measure, where standard preferences predict a fully
 contingent contract. The logic is that, due to the stochastic reference
 point, increasing the number of different wages reduces the agent's
 expected utility without providing strong additional incentives. Moreover,
 for diminutive occurrence probabilities for all signals the agent is
 rewarded with the fixed bonus if his performance exceeds a certain
 threshold. (JEL D82, D86, J41, M52, M12)
